62 SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> CollisionIntegral::load(
63  CollisionIntegral::ARGS args)
64 {
65  string type;
66  args.xml.getAttribute("type", type, "Integral type must be specified.");
67 
68  CollisionIntegral* p_ci;
69  try {
70  p_ci = Config::Factory<CollisionIntegral>::create(type, args);
71  } catch (Error& e) {
72  e << "\nWas trying to load a collision integral.";
73  throw;
74  }
75 
76  args.xml.parseCheck(p_ci != NULL,
77  "Invalid collision integral type '" + type + "' for " + args.kind +
78  "_" + args.pair.name() + ".");
79 
80  args.xml.parseCheck(p_ci->loaded(),
81  "Could not find data necessary to load " + args.kind +
82  "_" + args.pair.name() + ".");
83 
84  return SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral>(p_ci);
85 }

89 CollisionIntegral::CollisionIntegral(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
90  m_ref(""),
91  m_acc(0.0),
92  m_fac(1.0)
93 {
94  // Load the reference information if it exists
95  args.xml.getAttribute("ref", m_ref, m_ref);
96 
97  // Load the estimated accuracy if that exists
98  args.xml.getAttribute("accuracy", m_acc, m_acc);
99 
100  // Load any units that there might be
101  string units; args.xml.getAttribute("units", units, units);
102  if (!units.empty()) {
103  // Always take last units if available
104  std::vector<Units> vec = Units::split(units);
105  if (vec.size() == 0) args.xml.parseError(
106  "Invalid units attribute.");
107  m_units = vec.back();
108  }
109 
110  // Check if we should multiply by pi
111  bool multpi = false; args.xml.getAttribute("multpi", multpi, multpi);
112  m_fac = (multpi ? PI : 1.0);
113 }

116 
117 double CollisionIntegral::loadSpeciesParameter(
118  Mutation::Utilities::IO::XmlElement& root, const std::string& parameter,
119  const std::string& species, std::string units, double def)
120 {
121  // First look for the parameter table
122  XmlElement::const_iterator db_iter =
123  root.findTag(parameter);
124  if (db_iter == root.end())
125  return def;
126 
127  // Load default units if available
128  db_iter->getAttribute("units", units, units);
129 
130  // Check if the species name has an alias
131  std::string name = speciesAlias(root, species);
132 
133  // Look for species name
134  XmlElement::const_iterator sp_iter =
135  db_iter->findTagWithAttribute("species", "name", name);
136  if (sp_iter == db_iter->end())
137  return def;
138 
139  // Found it, get value
140  double value;
141  sp_iter->getAttribute("value", value, "must have a 'value' attribute.");
142 
143  // Check if units are different then the default
144  sp_iter->getAttribute("units", units, units);
145 
146  // Return value in base units
147  if (units.empty())
148  return value;
149 
150  return Units(units).convertToBase(value);
151 }

155 std::string CollisionIntegral::speciesAlias(
156  Mutation::Utilities::IO::XmlElement& root, const std::string& species)
157 {
158  // First look for the aliases list
159  XmlElement::const_iterator db_iter =
160  root.findTag("aliases");
161  if (db_iter == root.end())
162  return species;
163 
164  // Look for species name
165  XmlElement::const_iterator sp_iter =
166  db_iter->findTagWithAttribute("species", "name", species);
167  if (sp_iter == db_iter->end())
168  return species;
169 
170  // Get the alias name
171  std::string alias;
172  sp_iter->getAttribute("alias", alias, "must specify a species alias");
173  return alias;
174 }

265 class ExpPolyColInt : public CollisionIntegral
266 {
267 public:
268  ExpPolyColInt(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
269  CollisionIntegral(args)
270  {
271  // Load polynomial coefficients
272  std::stringstream ss(args.xml.text());
273 
274  std::copy(
275  std::istream_iterator<double>(ss),
276  std::istream_iterator<double>(),
277  std::back_inserter(m_params));
278  }
279 
280 private:
281 
282  double compute_(double T) {
283  double lnT = std::log(T);
284  double val = m_params[0];
285  for (int i = 1; i < m_params.size(); ++i)
286  val = val*lnT + m_params[i];
287  return std::exp(val);
288  }
289 
293  bool isEqual(const CollisionIntegral& ci) const {
294  const ExpPolyColInt& compare = dynamic_cast<const ExpPolyColInt&>(ci);
295  return (m_params == compare.m_params);
296  }

315 class FromAstColInt : public CollisionIntegral
316 {
317 public:
318  FromAstColInt(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
319  CollisionIntegral(args)
320  {
321  // Determine the type of B* expression to evaluate
322  string tag = args.xml.tag();
323  if (tag == "Ast") m_type = AST;
324  else if (tag == "Q11") m_type = Q11;
325  else if (tag == "Q22") m_type = Q22;
326  else args.xml.parseError(
327  "Cannot determine " + tag + " from A* expression");
328 
329  switch (m_type) {
330  case AST:
331  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Q11");
332  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q22");
333  break;
334  case Q11:
335  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Ast");
336  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q22");
337  break;
338  case Q22:
339  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Ast");
340  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q11");
341  break;
342  }
343  }
344 
346  bool loaded() const { return (m_ci1->loaded() && m_ci2->loaded()); }
347 
348  // Allow tabulation of this integral type
349  bool canTabulate() const {
350  return (m_ci1->canTabulate() && m_ci2->canTabulate());
351  }
352 
353  // Forward the getOtherParams call to the underlying integrals
354  void getOtherParams(const Thermodynamics::Thermodynamics& thermo) {
355  m_ci1->getOtherParams(thermo);
356  m_ci2->getOtherParams(thermo);
357  }
358 
359 private:
360 
361  enum AstType {
362  AST, Q11, Q22
363  };
364 
365  // Evaluate the A* expression
366  double compute_(double T) {
367  switch(m_type) {
368  case AST: return // Q22/Q11
369  (m_ci2->compute(T)/m_ci1->compute(T));
370  case Q11: return // Q22/A*
371  (m_ci2->compute(T)/m_ci1->compute(T));
372  case Q22: return // A* Q11
373  (m_ci1->compute(T)*m_ci2->compute(T));
374  }
375  return 0; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
376  }
377 
381  bool isEqual(const CollisionIntegral& ci) const {
382  const FromAstColInt& compare = dynamic_cast<const FromAstColInt&>(ci);
383  return (*m_ci1 == *(compare.m_ci1) && *m_ci2 == *(compare.m_ci2));
384  }
385 
386 private:
387 
388  AstType m_type;
389 
390  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_ci1;
391  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_ci2;
392 };
393 
394 // Register the "constant" CollisionIntegral
395 Config::ObjectProvider<FromAstColInt, CollisionIntegral> ast_ci("from A*");

404 class FromBstColInt : public CollisionIntegral
405 {
406 public:
407  FromBstColInt(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
408  CollisionIntegral(args)
409  {
410  // Determine the type of B* expression to evaluate
411  string tag = args.xml.tag();
412  if (tag == "Bst") m_type = BST;
413  else if (tag == "Q11") m_type = Q11;
414  else if (tag == "Q12") m_type = Q12;
415  else if (tag == "Q13") m_type = Q13;
416  else args.xml.parseError(
417  "Cannot determine " + tag + " from C* expression");
418 
419  switch (m_type) {
420  case BST:
421  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Q11");
422  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q12");
423  m_ci3 = args.pair.get("Q13");
424  break;
425  case Q11:
426  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Bst");
427  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q12");
428  m_ci3 = args.pair.get("Q13");
429  break;
430  case Q12:
431  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Bst");
432  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q11");
433  m_ci3 = args.pair.get("Q13");
434  break;
435  case Q13:
436  m_ci1 = args.pair.get("Bst");
437  m_ci2 = args.pair.get("Q11");
438  m_ci3 = args.pair.get("Q12");
439  break;
440  }
441  }
442 
444  bool loaded() const {
445  return (m_ci1->loaded() && m_ci2->loaded() && m_ci3->loaded());
446  }
447 
448  // Allow tabulation of this integral type
449  bool canTabulate() const {
450  return (m_ci1->canTabulate() &&
451  m_ci2->canTabulate() &&
452  m_ci3->canTabulate());
453  }
454 
455  // Forward the getOtherParams call to the underlying integrals
456  void getOtherParams(const Thermodynamics::Thermodynamics& thermo) {
457  m_ci1->getOtherParams(thermo);
458  m_ci2->getOtherParams(thermo);
459  m_ci3->getOtherParams(thermo);
460  }
461 
462 private:
463 
464  enum BstType {
465  BST, Q11, Q12, Q13
466  };
467 
468  // Evaluate the B* expression
469  double compute_(double T) {
470  switch(m_type) {
471  case BST: return // (5Q12 - 4Q13)/Q11
472  (5.*m_ci2->compute(T)-4.*m_ci3->compute(T))/m_ci1->compute(T);
473  case Q11: return // (5Q12 - 4Q13)/B*
474  (5.*m_ci2->compute(T)-4.*m_ci3->compute(T))/m_ci1->compute(T);
475  case Q12: return // (B*Q11 + 4Q13)/5
476  (m_ci1->compute(T)*m_ci2->compute(T)+4.*m_ci3->compute(T))/5.;
477  case Q13: return // (5*Q12 - B*Q11)/4
478  (5.*m_ci3->compute(T)-m_ci1->compute(T)*m_ci2->compute(T))/4.;
479  }
480  return 0; // LCOV_EXCL_LINE
481  }
482 
486  bool isEqual(const CollisionIntegral& ci) const {
487  const FromBstColInt& compare = dynamic_cast<const FromBstColInt&>(ci);
488  return (*m_ci1 == *(compare.m_ci1) &&
489  *m_ci2 == *(compare.m_ci2) &&
490  *m_ci3 == *(compare.m_ci3));
491  }
492 
493 private:
494 
495  BstType m_type;
496 
497  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_ci1;
498  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_ci2;
499  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_ci3;
500 };
501 
502 // Register the "constant" CollisionIntegral
503 Config::ObjectProvider<FromBstColInt, CollisionIntegral> bst_ci("from B*");

659 class MurphyColInt : public CollisionIntegral
660 {
661 public:
662  MurphyColInt(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
663  CollisionIntegral(args)
664  {
665  // Load the two integrals
666  m_Q1 = getIntegral(args, "Q1");
667  m_Q2 = getIntegral(args, "Q2");
668  }
669 
670  // Allow tabulation of this integral if the two underlying integrals can be
671  // tabulated
672  bool canTabulate() const {
673  return m_Q1->canTabulate() && m_Q2->canTabulate();
674  }
675 
679  bool isEqual(const CollisionIntegral& ci) const {
680  const MurphyColInt& compare = dynamic_cast<const MurphyColInt&>(ci);
681  return (*m_Q1 == *(compare.m_Q1) &&
682  *m_Q2 == *(compare.m_Q2));
683  }
684 
685 
686 private:
687 
688  double compute_(double T)
689  {
690  double Q1 = m_Q1->compute(T);
691  double Q2 = m_Q2->compute(T);
692  return std::sqrt(Q1*Q1 + Q2*Q2);
693  }
694 
695  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> getIntegral(
696  CollisionIntegral::ARGS args, const std::string& tag)
697  {
698  XmlElement::const_iterator Q = args.xml.findTag(tag);
699  if (Q == args.xml.end())
700  args.xml.parseError(
701  "Murphy collision integral must have " + tag + " child node.");
702 
703  return CollisionIntegral::load(
704  CollisionIntegral::ARGS(*Q, args.pair, args.kind));
705  }
706 
707 private:
708 
709  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_Q1;
710  SharedPtr<CollisionIntegral> m_Q2;
711 };

727 class TableColInt : public CollisionIntegral
728 {
729 public:
730  TableColInt(CollisionIntegral::ARGS args) :
731  CollisionIntegral(args),
732  m_interpolator_type("Linear"), m_clip(true)
733  {
734  // First load global options
735  loadGlobalOptions(args.xml.document()->root());
736 
737  // Check for the same options here
738  // clip
739  args.xml.getAttribute("clip", m_clip, m_clip);
740 
741  // interpolator
742  args.xml.getAttribute(
743  "interpolator", m_interpolator_type, m_interpolator_type);
744 
745  // Get the two vectors separated by a comma
746  vector<string> tokens;
747  String::tokenize(args.xml.text(), tokens, ",\n\r");
748 
749  if (tokens.size() != 2) args.xml.parseError(
750  "Incorrect format for collision integral table.");
751 
752  // Parse the two rows
753  fillVector(tokens[0], m_T);
754  fillVector(tokens[1], m_Q);
755 
756  if (m_T.size() != m_Q.size() && m_T.size() > 1) args.xml.parseError(
757  "Table rows must be same size and greater than 1.");
758 
759  // Load the interpolator
760  try {
761  mp_interpolator = SharedPtr< Interpolator<double> > (
762  Config::Factory<Interpolator<double> >::create(
763  m_interpolator_type,
764  Interpolator<double>::ARGS(&m_T[0], &m_Q[0], m_T.size())
765  ));
766  } catch (Error& e) {
767  e << "\nWas trying to load a collision integral interpolation "
768  << "scheme.";
769  throw;
770  }
771  }
772 
773  // Allow tabulation of this integral type
774  bool canTabulate() const { return true; }
775 
776 private:
777 
778  // Interpolate from a table
779  double compute_(double T)
780  {
781  // Clip the temperature if requested
782  if (m_clip) {
783  if (T < m_T[0])
784  return m_Q[0];
785  if (T > m_T.back())
786  return m_Q.back();
787  }
788 
789  return (*mp_interpolator)(T);
790  }
791 
795  bool isEqual(const CollisionIntegral& ci) const {
796  const TableColInt& compare = dynamic_cast<const TableColInt&>(ci);
797  return (m_T == compare.m_T && m_Q == compare.m_Q);
798  }
799 
803  void fillVector(const std::string& str, std::vector<double>& v) {
804  double val; istringstream ss(str);
805  while (ss >> val) v.push_back(val);
806  }
807 
808 private:
809 
810  void loadGlobalOptions(XmlElement& root)
811  {
812  // Look for global-options element
813  XmlElement::const_iterator options = root.findTag("global-options");
814  if (options == root.end()) return;
815 
816  // Look for table element
817  XmlElement::const_iterator table =
818  options->findTagWithAttribute("integral", "type", "table");
819  if (table == options->end()) return;
820 
821  // clip
822  table->getAttribute("clip", m_clip, m_clip);
823 
824  // interpolator
825  table->getAttribute(
826  "interpolator", m_interpolator_type, m_interpolator_type);
827  }
828 
829 private:
830 
831  vector<double> m_T;
832  vector<double> m_Q;
833 
834  SharedPtr< Interpolator<double> > mp_interpolator;
835  string m_interpolator_type;
836  bool m_clip;
837 
838 };
